  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.10.4">
<l>tāṅkarumpōr mālipaṭap paṟavai yūrntu tarātalattōr kuṟaimuṭitta taṉmai yāṉai</l>
<l>āṅkarumpik kaṇṇīrcōrn taṉpu kūru maṭiyavarkaṭ kāramuta māṉāṉ ṟaṉṉai</l>
<l>kōṅkarumpu curapuṉṉai kuravār cōlaik kuḻāvarivaṇ ṭicaipāṭum pāṭal kēṭṭu</l>
<l>tīṅkarumpu kaṇvaḷaruṅ kaḻaṉi cūḻnta tirukkōva lūrataṉuḷ kaṇṭēṉ nāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The one whose appearance destroyed the flaws of those of the earthly world,</l>
<l rend="indent">having ridden a bird when Māli died in a battle that was hard to bear,</l>
<l>The one who is rare nectar to the devotees whose love overflows,</l>
<l rend="indent">[their] tears thus bursting forth [and] falling,</l>
<l>I saw in Tirukkōvalūr, encircled by fields where sweet sugarcane</l>
<l rend="indent">with joints grows [high],</l>
<l>Hearing the songs that swarms of striped bees sing musically</l>
<l rend="indent">in groves filled with silk-cotton, budding forest laurel,</l>
<l rend="indent">and bottle flower [trees].</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
